This paper discusses the allocation of radio spectrum for wireless access, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The study also considers the impact on competition and congestion, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper analyzes the social and consumer welfare, which is related to communication and networking (cs.COM).
